pageContext.claim: “Georgia will be a big presidential win, as it was the night of the Election!”
pageContext.analysis: On election night, Trump was ahead by more than 100,000 votes, but there were nearly 270,000 ballots to be counted, mainly from Democratic strongholds. So Trump fell behind as more votes were counted. After a recount by the state's Republican governor and secretary of state, Biden eventually won by a margin of nearly 12,000 votes.
